{{Orphan|date=February 2017}}
The '''American Educational Resources Association (AERA)''' is an [[education]] resources organization in the [[United States|U.S.]] According to the group's [[website]], it was founded in 1916, and is research focused. The group publishes, issues awards, and holds meetings.<ref>AERA To Add Open-Access Research Journal (subscription required) Education Week, May 22, 2013</ref> The group is located in [[Washington, DC]].<ref>[http://www.aera.net/]</ref> The group has a site on [[Common Core Standards]]<ref>AERA Kicks Off Site on Common Standards Education Week, March 4, 2014</ref>
The group's publications have included ''Review of [[Educational research|Education Research]]''.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=ucd34PpVQ6EC&pg=PA285&dq=American+Education+Resources+Association%E2%80%8E&hl=en&sa=X&ei=tbU8U7LsM-vNsQTIiYLQAg&ved=0CEkQ6AEwCA#v=onepage&q=American%20Education%20Resources%20Association%E2%80%8E&f=false] page 285</ref>
