{{refimprove|date=June 2016}} {{use dmy dates|date=June 2016}} {{infobox school |name = Half Assini Senior High School |image = |imagesize = |caption = |alt = |location = [[Half Assini]], [[Western Region (Ghana)|Western Region]] |streetaddress = P. O. Box 60 |district = [[Jomoro District]] |postcode = |postalcode = |country = [[Ghana]] |coordinates = {{coord|5.05|-2.883333|format=dms|region:GH|display=inline,title}} |schoolnumber = |schoolboard = |authority = |category = B |oversight = [[Ministry of Education (Ghana)|Ministry of Education]] |affiliation = |authorizer = |superintendent = |trustee = |founder = [[Kwame Nkrumah]] |specialist = |session = |president = |headmaster = Mr. Edjah Kojo |head of school = |headteacher = |head_label = |head = |chairperson = |principal = |dean = |faculty = |administrator = |rector = |chaplain = |director = |staff = |ranking = |roll = |school code = |testaverage = |national_ranking = |classrooms = |class = |classes offered = Business, general arts, general science, home economics, visual arts |avg_class_size = 55 |ratio = |graduates = |gender = [[Co-educational]] |lower_age = 12 |upper_age = 18 |houses = 4 |schooltype = [[Public]] [[high school]] |fundingtype = |type = |system = |fees = |tuition = |revenue = |endowment = |budget = |products = |age range = |grades = |medium = |language = English |campus = |campus size = |campus type = |hours_in_Day = |athletics = |conference = |slogan = |song = |fightsong = |motto = Only the best is good for Africa |accreditation = [[Ghana Education Service]] |rival = |mascot image = |sports = |patron = |nickname = Osagyefo mba |school_colours = [[Blue]], [[yellow]] and [[white]] |mascot = [[Porcupine]] |yearbook = |publication = |newspaper = |established = {{start date and age|1960|8|12|df=yes|paren=yes}} |status = Active |students = |pupils = |alumni = Half Assini Secondary School Old Students Association (HASSOSA) |enrollment = 1,500+ |grade9 = |grade10 = |grade11 = |grade12 = |other = |communities = |feeders = |website = }} '''Half Assini Senior High School''' is a coeducational senior high school located at [[Half Assini]] in the [[Western Region (Ghana)|Western Region]] of [[Ghana]].<ref>{{Cite web|title = PTA provides school with lavatory|url = http://www.ghananewsagency.org/education/pta-provides-school-with-lavatory--89715|access-date = 22 May 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = Nzemas Celebrate Founder's Day – Daily Guide Ghana|url = http://www.dailyguideghana.com/nzemas-celebrate-founders-day/|website = www.dailyguideghana.com|access-date = 22 May 2015|deadurl = yes|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20150705125114/http://www.dailyguideghana.com/nzemas-celebrate-founders-day/|archivedate = 5 July 2015|df = dmy-all}}</ref>
==History== The school was one of the schools founded by the first [[president of Ghana]], Dr. [[Kwame Nkrumah]]. He founded the school with sixty students and four teachers. The school was among the few early established schools in the country (Modern Ghana) and it attracted the best of brains across the continent. Most of the infrastructure in the school now was originally put up by Nkrumah, and sincerely it had one of the best science resource centers in the country at the time.
==Student body== The school has about 1,500 students. {{clear}}
