{{Infobox school | name = Palau High School | type = High school | logo = PalauHSlogo.gif | image = Palau High School.JPG | students = | grades = | city = [[Koror City]] | country = Palau | district = [[Ministry of Education (Palau)]] | coordinates = {{coord|7.3419132|134.47086319999994|type:edu_globe:earth_region:PW|display=title,inline}} | pushpin_map = Palau | colors = | homepage = {{url|www.palaumoe.net/phs/}} }} '''Palau High School''' ('''PHS''') is a senior high school in [[Koror City]], [[Palau]]. It is the country's only public high school,<ref name=about>"[http://www.palaumoe.net/phs/about.php About]." Palau High School. Retrieved on February 22, 2018.</ref> and the first high school established in Palau.<ref>"[http://www.palaumoe.net/phs/index.php Home]." Palau High School. Retrieved on February 22, 2018.</ref> The [[Western Association of Schools and Colleges]] (WASC) accredits the school.<ref name=about/>
It opened as '''Palau Intermediate School''' in 1946. It previously was only for grades 6-9, but it was renamed and became a high school in 1962.<ref name=about/>
Its current building was built between the late 1960s to the middle of the 1970s, a period when several other public high schools were built in the [[Trust Territory of the Pacific Islands]].<ref>''Compact of Free Association in the Micronesian States of Palau, the Federated States of Micronesia and the Marshall Islands: Environmental Impact Statement''. [[United States Department of State]], 1984. p. [https://books.google.ca/books?id=_6g4AQAAMAAJ&pg=PA36 36].</ref>
